description: Squarefree n such that the elliptic curve n*y^2 = x^3 - x arising in the "congruent number" problem has rank 3 and nontrivial SHA[2].
comments: Conjectural, as detailed in the pages from which it is extracted (see the first few links at the web site mentioned for details), but the conjecture is supported by much numerical and theoretical evidence.
links: N. D. Elkies, Algorithmic (a.k.a. Computational) Number Theory: Tables, Links, etc.
author: _Noam D. Elkies_, Jul 04 2001
